## Suggested `Makefile` targets

Add these:

```makefile
new-rule:
	@$(VENV_PY) tools/new_rule.py \
		--catalog "$(CATALOG)" \
		--categories "$(CATEGORIES)" \
		--families "$(FAMILIES)" \
		--family "$(FAMILY)" \
		--layer "$(LAYER)" \
		--tier "$(TIER)" \
		--severity "$(SEVERITY)"

new-rule-append:
	@$(VENV_PY) tools/new_rule.py \
		--catalog "$(CATALOG)" \
		--categories "$(CATEGORIES)" \
		--families "$(FAMILIES)" \
		--family "$(FAMILY)" \
		--layer "$(LAYER)" \
		--tier "$(TIER)" \
		--severity "$(SEVERITY)" \
		--append \
		--sort-rules
````

## Example usage

Create stubs only:

```bash
make new-rule FAMILY=Python LAYER=Code TIER=1 SEVERITY=medium
```

Create stubs and append to `master.json`:

```bash
make new-rule-append FAMILY=Python LAYER=Code TIER=1 SEVERITY=medium
```

## Recommended workflow

I’d use this sequence:

```bash
make new-rule-append FAMILY=Python LAYER=Code TIER=1 SEVERITY=medium
python tools/update_rules.py --catalog master.json --categories ontology/categories.json --families ontology/families.json --write --fill-system-layer --normalize-ontology
python tools/check_all.py --strict
make docs
```

If you want, I can also give you a companion `tools/merge_rule_stub.py` so contributors can edit the generated JSON stub first and merge it later without using `--append` up front.

